covered: Valid Request: Scenarios test successful retrieval with default params (TC01) and with various valid parameter combinations (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC07, TC09, TC11, TC12, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC18, TC21, TC22, TC25, TC26, TC42, TC43, TC47, TC48, TC50).
N/A Response/Empty Data: Scenarios cover empty results (TC08, TC09) and partial data (TC30, TC46, TC50).
Pagination Basics: Tests for offset/limit usage (TC02, TC07, TC21, TC43, TC47, TC49, TC50) and boundary behavior (TC21, TC46, TC47, TC49).
Query Parameters: Variety of parameters tested (offset, limit, accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, audit).
Error Handling: Invalid parameter values (TC10, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC23, TC39, TC40, TC24), malformed/invalid requests (TC39, TC40), and unsupported extra parameters (TC14, TC29).
Security: Injection and XSS scenarios (TC23, TC24).
Resilience/Recovery: Network timeout (TC18), transient network recovery (TC36), dependency recovery (TC37).
Performance: Large data volume (TC19), degraded system under load (TC31).
Concurrency/Integrity: Concurrent requests (TC20), data consistency with audit log (TC33).
Integration: Dependency/service unavailability (TC32, TC42), audit log alignment (TC33).
State variations: Partially populated database (TC30), edge case parameter handling (TC25, TC27, TC28).
gaps: Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache behavior.
Rate Limiting: No explicit tests for rate limiting or throttling under high request volume.
recommendations: Add tests to validate caching headers presence and correctness (ETag, Cache-Control) and behavior on subsequent requests (TC34 touches accessibility but not caching).
Introduce explicit rate-limiting/throttling tests (e.g., multiple rapid requests to ensure proper handling).
Consider dedicated tests for 403 (forbidden) vs 401 (unauthorized) to cover more authorization scenarios.
Include a test ensuring 414/413 behavior when query string becomes excessively large, beyond current TC41 scope (edge case with large payloads in query).
Add targeted tests for boundary conditions not fully exercised, such as max/min offset and limit combinations under concurrent load (beyond TC21/TC49/TC50).
Optional: add a focused test verifying behavior when audit parameter is omitted (already touched in TC45, but could be consolidated with default behavior).
